Writes the specified data followed by a newline to the standard output.
```csharp
Console.WriteLine("Hello World");
Console.WriteLine($"Name: {name}, Age: {age}");
Console.WriteLine(42);
```

Adds an object to the end of the list.
```csharp
var list = new List<string>();
list.Add("Alice");
list.Add("Bob");
```

Adds the specified key-value pair to the dictionary.
```csharp
var dict = new Dictionary<string, int>();
dict.Add("age", 30);
```

Converts the string representation of a number to its 32-bit signed integer equivalent. Throws `FormatException` on failure.
```csharp
int n = int.Parse("42");
int n2 = int.Parse("-100");
```

Queues work to run on the thread pool and returns a `Task`.
```csharp
Task task = Task.Run(() => DoWork());
Task<int> result = Task.Run(() => Compute());
await Task.Run(() => HeavyOperation());
```

Projects each element of a sequence into a new form (LINQ).
```csharp
var names = people.Select(p => p.Name);
var doubled = numbers.Select(n => n * 2);
var indexed = items.Select((item, i) => $"{i}: {item}");
```

Filters a sequence of values based on a predicate (LINQ).
```csharp
var adults = people.Where(p => p.Age >= 18);
var evens = numbers.Where(n => n % 2 == 0);
```
